# Testing Standards

## Philosophy

- Tests are first-class code — they are read, maintained, and refactored just like production code
- Tests document intended behavior; they are the living specification
- A failing test is always a signal — never silently skip or comment out tests
- Tests must be **deterministic**: same input → same output, every time, on every machine

## Test Types & Coverage Targets

| Type | What it tests | Speed | Mocking | Coverage target |
|------|--------------|-------|---------|-----------------|
| **Unit** | Single function / class in isolation | < 1ms | Mock all I/O | 90%+ of business logic |
| **Integration** | Multiple components together | 100ms–2s | Real DB, mock HTTP | All API endpoints |
| **E2E** | Full user journey | 2–30s | None | Critical user paths |

